com.ibm.team.scm.common

Interface IFlowEntry


  • public interface IFlowEntry
    An entry in a flow table.

    The following uses are currently supported:

    • The target is a flow node IFlowNodeHandle and there are no component scopes. This entry describes the normal flow between a workspace and the workspace (or stream) listed as the primary target.
    • The primary target is a workspace IWorkspaceHandle and the additional component scopes are specified IComponentHandle. This entry describes the normal flow between a workspace and the workspace listed as the primary target confined to the components listed as scopes. An entry for a specific component overrides any non-specific entry.

    Since:
    0.5
    See Also:
    IFlowTable
